An Act to enforce laws protecting worksite safety.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 29 of chapter 149 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting the following new section:
3 “A party to a contract for construction having a duty, whether by law or by contract, to
4 maintain a safe workplace or to comply with applicable safety standards, may not transfer the
5 responsibility to pay for, defend against, or provide insurance covering claims, liabilities, fines,
6 or damages to the extent caused by that party’s breach of such duty. Any provision in a contract
7 for construction which purports to transfer any such responsibility shall be void and
8 unenforceable as against public policy.”
